  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can take a Magic action to exhale the draconic energies within you much like a dragon's breath weapon. Your draconic ancestry determines the damage type of the exhalation. When you use your breath weapon, each creature in the area of the exhalation must make a Dexterity saving throw. You can choose the area of your breath weapon to be a 5 by 30 ft. line or 15 ft. cone each time you use the feature.</p><p>The DC for this saving throw equals 8 plus your Charisma modifier plus your Proficiency Bonus. A creature takes a number of d6s equal to half your Sorcerer level in damage on a failed save, and half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>Once you use your breath weapon, you cannot use it again until you finish a Long Rest, unless you spend 4 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore your use of it.</p>",
